# Clean Code Patterns — museothyssen

## Core principle

**Low nesting, high readability.** In this theme, UI lives in **Twig (SDC)**; interactivity in **TypeScript** (`Drupal.behaviors` + `once`). Do not mix responsibilities across layers.

| Layer | Files | Responsibility |
|------|----------|-----------------|
| **SDC** | `components/{tier}/{name}/{name}.twig` (`tier`: `atoms` \| `molecules` \| `organisms`) | Markup, Tailwind classes, composition of other SDCs |
| **Schema** | `{name}.component.yml` | Props, examples, Storybook, library dependencies |
| **Behavior** | `components/{tier}/{name}/js/{name}.ts` | DOM, events, ARIA (only when JS is needed) |
| **Layout** | `templates/**/*.twig` | Regions, pages, grids — not atom styles |

## Twig: extract instead of nesting

### ❌ Before: deep branches in one file

```twig
{% for item in items %}
  <div>
    {% if item.url and not loop.last %}
      <a href="{{ item.url }}">{{ item.label }}</a>
    {% else %}
      <span>{{ item.label }}</span>
    {% endif %}
  </div>
{% endfor %}
```

### ✅ After: dedicated macro or include

```twig
{% macro breadcrumb_item(item, is_last) %}
  {% if item.url and not is_last %}
    <a href="{{ item.url }}">{{ item.label }}</a>
  {% else %}
    <span aria-current="{{ is_last ? 'page' : false }}">{{ item.label }}</span>
  {% endif %}
{% endmacro %}

{% for item in items %}
  <li>{{ _self.breadcrumb_item(item, loop.last) }}</li>
{% endfor %}
```

For large blocks (e.g. image with render array vs `canvas:image`), follow `hello.twig` / `promo_banner.twig`: **one `{% if %}` block per case**, brief comment, no duplicated wrapper.

## TypeScript (behaviors): small functions

### ❌ Before: long logic inside `attach`

```ts
once("id", ".root", context).forEach((root) => {
  const btn = root.querySelector("button");
  if (!btn) return;
  btn.addEventListener("click", () => {
  /* many lines */
  });
});
```

### ✅ After: helpers with early return

```ts
function bindHelloToggle(root: HTMLElement): void {
  const toggle = root.querySelector<HTMLButtonElement>("[data-hello-toggle]");
  const subtitle = root.querySelector<HTMLElement>(".museothyssen-hello__subtitle");
  if (!toggle || !subtitle) {
    return;
  }
  toggle.addEventListener("click", () => { /* ... */ });
}

attach(context) {
  once("museothyssen-hello", ".museothyssen-hello", context).forEach(bindHelloToggle);
}
```

Reuse utilities in `js/utils/` (e.g. `toggleDataState`).

## Key rules

- **At most 2–3 levels** of `{% if %}` / `{% for %}` in one template.
- **One responsibility per SDC**: do not put page layout inside an atom.
- **BEM names + theme prefix**: `museothyssen-{component}__element`.
- **Compose SDCs** with `{% include 'museothyssen:action_link' with { ... } only %}` instead of copying markup.
- **Clause guards in TS**: `if (!el) return;` — see also `typescript-critical-rules.mdc`.

## Props in `*.component.yml`

- **`examples`** on each relevant prop (Storybook and docs).
- **`required`** only for what is mandatory; everything else with `default` or optional.
- Visual variants → `thirdPartySettings.sdcStorybook.stories`, not duplicate Twig branches per variant.

## Creating new components

```bash
ddev drush generate single-directory-component
```

Naming conventions: see `sdc.mdc` (singular, English, descriptive).
